        "title: \"Module 1 - Tutorial 2\"\n",
        "subtitle: \"From Clean SEC Text to TF-IDF Features\"\n",
        "number-sections: true\n",
        "date: \"2026-02-01\"\n",
        "date-modified: today\n",
        "date-format: long\n",
        "engine: jupyter\n",
        "format:\n",
        "  html:\n",
        "    code-overflow: wrap\n",
        "categories: [\"M01:\", \"Tutorial\", \"SEC Text\", \"TF-IDF\"]\n",
        "description: \"Tutorial for Module 1 focused on turning cleaned SEC text into a simple feature matrix that supports the labs and Assignment 1.\"\n",
        "execute:\n",
        "  echo: true\n",
        "  eval: false\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## Module Learning Objectives {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "By the end of Module 1, students should be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. preprocess SEC text consistently\n",
        "2. build interpretable count-based feature representations\n",
        "3. compare classical and neural-ready text pipelines\n",
        "4. prepare reusable artifacts for assignment work\n",
        "\n",
        "## Tutorial Learning Objectives {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "By the end of this tutorial you will be able to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Load a small SEC text sample for one or two companies.\n",
        "2. Clean and tokenize text consistently.\n",
        "3. Build a vocabulary and simple document-term counts.\n",
        "4. Convert those counts into TF-IDF features.\n",
        "5. Interpret top words before moving to the full Assignment 1 workflow.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Recommended Dataset {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "Use one of the following:\n",
        "\n",
        "- a small sample of SEC 10-K text for a single company\n",
        "- a few files from `data/SEC-10K-2024`\n",
        "- a few extracted sections from Item 1A or Item 7\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal is to learn the workflow on a small scale before the full assignment corpus.\n",
        "\n",
        "## How This Tutorial Connects {.unnumbered}\n",
        "\n",
        "- `M01_Lab1` focuses on preprocessing discipline and text inspection.\n",
        "- `M01_Lab2` introduces representation learning and embeddings.\n",
        "- `M01_A` expects students to build reusable SEC text features at larger scale.\n",
        "- Module 1 participation work can use the same cleaned text and vocabulary logic.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Setup {.unnumbered}"
      ],
      "id": "c2061e8d"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "from pathlib import Path\n",
        "from collections import Counter\n",
        "import re\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer"
      ],
      "id": "e690fbe0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 1: Load a Small SEC Sample {.unnumbered}"
      ],
      "id": "b4a4f974"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "sample_dir = Path(\"../data/SEC-10K-2024\")\n",
        "txt_files = sorted(sample_dir.glob(\"*.txt\"))[:3]\n",
        "\n",
        "docs = []\n",
        "for f in txt_files:\n",
        "    text = f.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\", errors=\"ignore\")\n",
        "    docs.append({\"source\": f.stem, \"text\": text[:12000]})\n",
        "\n",
        "sample_df = pd.DataFrame(docs)\n",
        "sample_df.head()"
      ],
      "id": "a16e6f26",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 2: Clean the Text {.unnumbered}"
      ],
      "id": "c4926cfa"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "def clean_text(text: str) -> str:\n",
        "    text = text.lower()\n",
        "    text = re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9\\\\s]\", \" \", text)\n",
        "    text = re.sub(r\"\\\\s+\", \" \", text).strip()\n",
        "    return text\n",
        "\n",
        "sample_df[\"clean_text\"] = sample_df[\"text\"].apply(clean_text)\n",
        "sample_df[[\"source\", \"clean_text\"]].head()"
      ],
      "id": "21247ab0",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 3: Build a Simple Vocabulary View {.unnumbered}"
      ],
      "id": "c0597465"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "all_tokens = \" \".join(sample_df[\"clean_text\"]).split()\n",
        "token_counts = Counter(all_tokens)\n",
        "pd.DataFrame(token_counts.most_common(20), columns=[\"token\", \"count\"])"
      ],
      "id": "66cd5b57",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 4: Create TF-IDF Features {.unnumbered}"
      ],
      "id": "361d05b0"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(max_features=500, stop_words=\"english\")\n",
        "X = vectorizer.fit_transform(sample_df[\"clean_text\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "tfidf_df = pd.DataFrame(X.toarray(), columns=vectorizer.get_feature_names_out())\n",
        "tfidf_df.insert(0, \"source\", sample_df[\"source\"])\n",
        "tfidf_df.head()"
      ],
      "id": "b5a0920b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## Step 5: Interpret Top Terms {.unnumbered}"
      ],
      "id": "bd1cf728"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "mean_scores = tfidf_df.drop(columns=\"source\").mean().sort_values(ascending=False).head(20)\n",
        "mean_scores"
      ],
      "id": "d114a14b",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
